    "author": "maya-chen",
    "date": "2026-06-29",
    "title": "iPhone 18 Pro: everything we know so far",
    "dek": "A 2nm A20 Pro chip, a variable-aperture camera and a fall 2026 launch — here is what the credible leaks actually point to.",
    "image": "img/iphone-18-pro-everything-we-know.jpg",
    "imageAlt": "A modern smartphone resting on a desk next to accessories",
    "imageCredit": "Illustration: GadgetPulse",
    "tags": ["iPhone 18 Pro", "Apple", "smartphones"],
    "body": [
      {"type":"p","text":"Apple's fall lineup is shaping up to be its biggest shake-up in years. With WWDC 2026 behind us and dummy units already circulating, the outline of the iPhone 18 Pro is fairly clear — and for the first time Apple looks set to split its launch."},
      {"type":"p","text":"Here is what has a real paper trail versus what is still wishful thinking, and what each change would mean in everyday use."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"A 2nm A20 Pro chip"},
      {"type":"p","text":"The 18 Pro is expected to move to a 2-nanometer A20 Pro, a genuine step down from the A19's 3nm process. The practical win is efficiency — more battery life at the same speed — paired with a vapor chamber carried over for sustained performance under load."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Cameras get the biggest upgrade"},
      {"type":"ul","items":["Variable-aperture main camera for real depth-of-field control","A 200MP main sensor expected on the Pro Max","A sharper 24MP front camera across the line","Storage reportedly up to 2TB on the Pro Max"]},
      {"type":"h2","text":"A split launch"},
      {"type":"p","text":"Multiple reports say only the Pro models — alongside Apple's first foldable, the iPhone Ultra — will arrive in September 2026, while the standard iPhone 18 slips to spring 2027. Expect higher Pro pricing too."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Should you wait?"},
      {"type":"p","text":"If you are on a 16 Pro or older, the camera and efficiency gains make waiting sensible. Coming from a 17 Pro, it is a smaller jump."}
    ],
    "faq": [
      {"q":"When will the iPhone 18 Pro be released?","a":"Reports point to a September 2026 launch for the Pro models, with the standard iPhone 18 expected in spring 2027."},
      {"q":"What chip will the iPhone 18 Pro use?","a":"A 2nm A20 Pro chip is widely expected, a step down from the A19's 3nm process."},
      {"q":"What is the biggest iPhone 18 Pro upgrade?","a":"A variable-aperture main camera and, on the Pro Max, a 200MP sensor are the headline changes."}
    ],
    "sources": [
      {"title":"MacRumors — iPhone 18 roundup","url":"https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-18/"},
      {"title":"9to5Mac — iPhone 18 Pro vs Ultra","url":"https://9to5mac.com/2026/05/28/iphone-18-pro-vs-iphone-ultra-three-features-to-win-your-upgrade/"}
    ]
  },
  {
    "slug": "iphone-18-pro-vs-iphone-ultra",
    "cluster": "phones",
    "author": "maya-chen",
    "date": "2026-06-28",
    "title": "iPhone 18 Pro vs iPhone Ultra: which to wait for",
    "dek": "Apple's first foldable, the iPhone Ultra, sits above the Pro for the first time — same chip, very different bodies. Here is how they compare.",
    "image": "img/iphone-18-pro-vs-iphone-ultra.jpg",
    "imageAlt": "Two premium smartphones side by side on a table",
    "imageCredit": "Illustration: GadgetPulse",
    "tags": ["iPhone Ultra", "iPhone 18 Pro", "foldable"],
    "body": [
      {"type":"p","text":"For the first time, Apple is placing a new Ultra tier above the Pro Max — and it is a foldable. Both phones share the A20 Pro, but materials and design pull them in different directions."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Performance: same chip, different thermals"},
      {"type":"p","text":"Both are expected to run the A20 Pro. But the 18 Pro keeps an aluminum unibody with a vapor chamber, while the Ultra uses a thinner titanium build without one — so the Ultra may throttle sooner under heavy load or in direct sun."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Design and price"},
      {"type":"ul","items":["iPhone Ultra: foldable, titanium, around 11mm thick closed, rumored up to $2,500, possibly without MagSafe","iPhone 18 Pro: familiar slab design, vapor-chamber cooling, a lower price"]},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Launch timing"},
      {"type":"p","text":"The 18 Pro is expected in September. The Ultra's foldable display is reportedly harder to produce, so it may ship slightly later in the cycle."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Which should you wait for?"},
      {"type":"p","text":"Want the best sustained performance and value, go for the 18 Pro. Want the novelty of Apple's first fold and can stomach the premium, the Ultra is the halo device."}
    ],
    "faq": [
      {"q":"How much will the iPhone Ultra cost?","a":"Reports suggest up to around $2,500, which would make it Apple's most expensive iPhone."},
      {"q":"Is the iPhone Ultra a foldable?","a":"Yes — it is expected to be Apple's first foldable iPhone, positioned above the Pro Max."},
      {"q":"Do the iPhone 18 Pro and Ultra use the same chip?","a":"Both are expected to use the A20 Pro, though their thermal designs differ."}
    ],
    "sources": [
      {"title":"9to5Mac — iPhone 18 Pro vs Ultra","url":"https://9to5mac.com/2026/05/28/iphone-18-pro-vs-iphone-ultra-three-features-to-win-your-upgrade/"},
      {"title":"Macworld — separate launches confirmed","url":"https://www.macworld.com/article/3177251/iphone-18-and-ultra-to-have-separate-launches-sources-confirm.html"}
    ]
