  {
    "slug": "smart-home-go-local-matter-2026",
    "cluster": "smart-home",
    "author": "maya-chen",
    "date": "2026-06-27",
    "title": "Build a smart home in 2026: go local with Matter",
    "dek": "The single best upgrade this year is not a gadget — it is moving your automations local. Here is a no-lock-in starter plan.",
    "image": "img/smart-home-go-local-matter-2026.jpg",
    "imageAlt": "A smart speaker and smart bulb in a living room",
    "imageCredit": "Illustration: GadgetPulse",
    "tags": ["smart home", "Matter", "IoT"],
    "body": [
      {"type":"p","text":"The smart home matured in 2026, and the biggest improvement you can make costs nothing: run things locally. Matter keeps smoothing cross-brand compatibility, and platforms from Home Assistant to Apple Home are leaning into local execution."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Why local wins"},
      {"type":"p","text":"Local automations fire instantly, keep working during internet outages, and leak less data than cloud-dependent setups. When buying anything new, look for the Matter logo and confirm the device can run locally."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"The three essentials"},
      {"type":"ul","items":["A hub or smart speaker to act as the controller","A couple of Matter-certified smart bulbs for the rooms you use most","One smart plug to automate a lamp or coffee maker"]},
      {"type":"h2","text":"A note of caution"},
      {"type":"p","text":"Matter still is not perfect — setup quirks and uneven device support remain. Buy from established brands and check local support before committing to a whole system."}
    ],
    "faq": [
      {"q":"What is the best smart home upgrade in 2026?","a":"Moving automations to local execution using Matter devices that do not depend on the cloud is the most-cited upgrade."},
      {"q":"Is Matter reliable in 2026?","a":"It has improved a lot but still has rough edges; buying established Matter-certified devices reduces headaches."}
    ],
    "sources": [
      {"title":"Forbes — supercharge your smart home in 2026","url":"https://www.forbes.com/sites/paullamkin/2026/01/01/how-to-supercharge-your-smart-home-in-2026/"},
      {"title":"matter-smarthome — Matter status in 2026","url":"https://matter-smarthome.de/en/development/the-matter-standard-in-2026-a-status-review/"}
    ]
  },
  {
    "slug": "nintendo-switch-2-one-year-later",
    "cluster": "gaming",
    "author": "alex-rivera",
    "date": "2026-06-26",
    "title": "Nintendo Switch 2, one year later: still worth it?",
    "dek": "A year after launch and on firmware 22.5, the Switch 2 looks like a stronger buy than it did in 2025 — even as rivals raise prices.",
    "image": "img/nintendo-switch-2-one-year-later.jpg",
    "imageAlt": "A handheld gaming console held in two hands",
    "imageCredit": "Illustration: GadgetPulse",
    "tags": ["Nintendo Switch 2", "handheld", "gaming"],
    "body": [
      {"type":"p","text":"A year on, the Switch 2 has settled into its stride. With a healthy exclusive lineup — Mario Kart World alone passed 14.7 million copies — and steady firmware updates, it is a more convincing buy than it was at launch."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Why it looks better now"},
      {"type":"p","text":"The library has filled out, performance is stable, and price increases elsewhere — Valve recently raised Steam Deck prices — make the Switch 2 look reasonable for a mid-range handheld."},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Switch 2 vs Switch OLED"},
      {"type":"ul","items":["Switch 2: far more power, backward compatible, bigger screen","Switch OLED: cheaper, gorgeous screen, great battery for lighter games"]},
      {"type":"h2","text":"Who should buy"},
      {"type":"p","text":"If you want Nintendo exclusives and modern performance, the Switch 2 is the pick. If you only play lighter titles and want the best screen-per-dollar, the OLED still holds up."}
    ],
    "faq": [
      {"q":"Is the Nintendo Switch 2 worth it in 2026?","a":"A year after launch, with a stronger library and stable performance, most buyers find it worth it — especially for Nintendo exclusives."},
      {"q":"Switch 2 or Switch OLED for handheld?","a":"The Switch 2 is far more powerful; the OLED is cheaper with a great screen and battery for lighter games."}
    ],
    "sources": [
      {"title":"CNET — Switch 2 one year on","url":"https://www.cnet.com/tech/gaming/one-year-on-nintendos-switch-2-impresses-me-more-than-ever/"},
